# Robust Testing Pipeline & Quality Assurance Plan

This plan outlines the creation of a high-tier testing infrastructure for the IQ Option trading bot, targeting 100% code coverage, zero-tolerance for warnings/linting errors, and deep validation of trading logic.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **API Credentials for Integration Tests**: To perform real API validation without risking funds, we will use the **Practice Account**. 100% coverage requires simulating edge cases (API timeouts, invalid orders, connection drops) which will be handled via a hybrid approach of Mocking and real Practice account interactions.

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Infrastructure Setup
- Create a `tests/` directory following standard Python patterns.
- Install and configure `pytest`, `pytest-cov`, `pytest-mock`, and `linting` tools (`flake8`, `mypy`).
- Configure a [.coveragerc](file:///C:/Users/uz02095/Documents/BotIQOpt_/.coveragerc) to track total project coverage.

### 2. Unit Testing Layer (Syntactic & Logical)
- **Ferramental**: Comprehensive test suite reaching >80% coverage.
- **main.py**: Flow validation and error handling coverage.

### 3. Integration Testing Layer (Semantic & Hermeneutic)
- **API Wrapper**: Implement a Mock layer for `iqoptionapi` to test how [Ferramental](file:///C:/Users/uz02095/Documents/BotIQOpt_/ferramental/Ferramental.py#115-1814) interprets diverse API responses (Success, Failure, Multi-factor auth required).
- **Data Flow**: Test the integration between [Ferramental](file:///C:/Users/uz02095/Documents/BotIQOpt_/ferramental/Ferramental.py#115-1814) data retrieval and [Inteligencia](file:///C:/Users/uz02095/Documents/BotIQOpt_/inteligencia/Inteligencia.py#106-1539) processing.

### 4. End-to-End & Philosophical Layer
- **Full Flow Execution**: A test suite that runs a simulated trading session from login to order confirmation.
- **Risk Management Boundaries**: Stress testing the bot's reaction to consecutive losses and daily profit limits.
- **Philosophical Consistency**: Verification that every trade adheres to the "Safety First" principle (Stop Loss, Take Profit validation).

### 5. Zero-Tolerance Quality Audit
- **Ferramental Integrity**: alcançado 86% de cobertura em core, [get_balance](file:///C:/Users/uz02095/Documents/BotIQOpt_/tests/integration/mock_api.py#22-24), [reconnect](file:///C:/Users/uz02095/Documents/BotIQOpt_/ferramental/Ferramental.py#267-275), e lógica de simulação simplificada. Atributos inicializados no `__init__` para evitar `AttributeError`.
- **Intelligence Validation**: 
    - [x] Unidade de testes para [LSTMModel](file:///C:/Users/uz02095/Documents/BotIQOpt_/inteligencia/Inteligencia.py#24-101) (forward pass, weight init, device handling).
    - [x] Unidade de testes para `DataLoader` e engenharia de recursos ([_add_technical_indicators](file:///C:/Users/uz02095/Documents/BotIQOpt_/inteligencia/Inteligencia.py#993-1106), [_add_candle_patterns](file:///C:/Users/uz02095/Documents/BotIQOpt_/inteligencia/Inteligencia.py#1108-1175)).
    - [ ] 100% cobertura em pipelines de dados e loops de treinamento/inferência (atualmente 83%).
- **Zero Errors**: 
    - [ ] Fix all 100+ `flake8` violations in [Inteligencia.py](file:///C:/Users/uz02095/Documents/BotIQOpt_/inteligencia/Inteligencia.py) (repetitive blank lines, line lengths, indentation).
    - [ ] Resolve type errors and runtime warnings.



## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- `pytest --cov=. --cov-report=term-missing`
- `flake8 .`
- `mypy .`

### Manual Verification
- Execution of a "Dry Run" test cycle where the bot operates in Practice mode, and results are manually audited against expected terminal outputs.
